# Mobile-First App Design

## Core Layout
- All application content must be wrapped in a `#phone-frame` container.
- **Dimensions:** Fixed aspect ratio of 19.5:9 (e.g., 390px x 844px for iPhone 14/15 Pro).
- **Safe Areas:** Implement variables for the "Notch" (top: 47px) and "Home Indicator" (bottom: 34px).

## iPhone Frame CSS Blueprint
Apply the following structure to the root layout:

```css
:root {
  --phone-width: 390px;
  --phone-height: 844px;
  --safe-top: 47px;
  --safe-bottom: 34px;
  --iphone-radius: 40px;
}

#phone-frame {
  width: var(--phone-width);
  height: var(--phone-height);
  border: 12px solid #222;
  border-radius: var(--iphone-radius);
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: #fff;
  box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
  margin: 20px auto;
}

#app-content {
  height: 100%;
  overflow-y: auto;
  padding-top: var(--safe-top);
  padding-bottom: var(--safe-bottom);
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
}

/* The "Notch" / Dynamic Island */
#phone-frame::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 15px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 120px;
  height: 30px;
  background: #222;
  border-radius: 20px;
  z-index: 100;
}